mdview v{{VERSION}}
Markdown viewer plugin for Total Commander
(Mermaid diagrams, TeX math via KaTeX, syntax highlighting)

WHAT'S IN THIS ZIP
  mdview.wlx     32-bit plugin (used by 32-bit Total Commander)
  mdview.wlx64   64-bit plugin (used by 64-bit Total Commander)
  pluginst.inf   Total Commander auto-install manifest
  README.txt     this file

INSTALL (recommended)
  1. Open this .zip inside Total Commander (Ctrl+PageDown on it,
     or drag it onto a panel).
  2. Total Commander detects pluginst.inf and offers to install
     the plugin. Accept.
  3. Press F3 on any .md / .markdown / .mdown / .mkd file.

  Total Commander automatically uses the binary matching its own
  bitness; both are installed.

MANUAL INSTALL (fallback)
  Copy the binary matching your Total Commander bitness into a
  folder under TC's plugin directory, e.g.
    ...\plugins\wlx\mdview\mdview.wlx     (32-bit TC)
    ...\plugins\wlx\mdview\mdview.wlx64   (64-bit TC)
  then add it under Configuration -> Options -> Edit/View/Search
  -> Lister Plugins. Detect string:
    EXT="MD" | EXT="MARKDOWN" | EXT="MDOWN" | EXT="MKD"

REQUIREMENTS
  - Total Commander (32- or 64-bit).
  - Microsoft Edge WebView2 Runtime (preinstalled on current
    Windows 11; otherwise:
    https://developer.microsoft.com/microsoft-edge/webview2/ ).
  - No Visual C++ redistributable needed (runtime linked static).
  - Windows 7 SP1 / 8.1: works, but only with the last WebView2
    runtime those systems support (v109). That build has had no
    security updates since October 2023. Use at your own risk.

